Heya! Thanks for reminding me to put aniDB to planned services that I accidentally forgot to list it (lol)
However, although yes I could able to possibly integrate aniDB mylist as I learned a lot of stuff on Python for a year now, I have some concern regarding aniDB itself.
aniDB developer experience is really archaic at best. Their API access mainly uses UDP protocol which I'd say, none of the services used it but aniDB, and even sending the command to its API must be really careful. If the command were sent simultaneously without delay, oh boy, your account or even your IP address can get banned. Additionally, I personally don't know how to handle UDP commands, so using it might require me to sacrifice my IP instead.
Although they have read-only HTTP API, it only applicable for Anime information instead, not all-purpose.
Scraping HTML of mylist can risk of your account/ip to get banned, so I definitely want to avoid this, as the aniDB maintainers themselves explicitly didn't allow html scrapping. bokusu will be intended as Async-based package module/cli app since I want to make this module to be supported to my another Anime program project, miirakuru. Most of the libraries available in pypi are sync-based, which could break bokusu .
Those all are my concerns about aniDB to be integrated to the module. I can make an opt-in system to allow scraping html of mylist, however no support will be given if anything happened to the account/IP.

div.div: Isekai de Mofumofu Nadenade Suru Tame ni Ganbattemasu.

Dead of overwork at age 27... Midori barely had time to lament having to die that way when a god appeared before her and said, "You will reincarnate in another world and tell me whether you think humans deserve to continue existing there. In return, I will grant you a special power." Then Midori, hoping to relieve the exhaustion of the harsh life she'd lived, found herself asking... to cuddle cute, fluffy animals. Thus Midori reincarnated in her new world as a young girl named Nefertima, with a power that causes her to be loved by all living things other than humans. That includes not only animals, but holy beasts like white tigers and dragons, and even monsters like goblins and frozen spiders! But there was also a cruel fate awaiting her... Nefertima is determined to do her best to coexist with humans and all living creatures in her new life of petting and patting cute animals! (Source: Crunchyroll) Note: Each episode streamed 1 week early on ABEMA. The original TV broadcast started on January 7th, 2024.
Comedy, Drama, Sci-Fi, Slice of Life

"I've been holding a few words back for a long time — I like you!" "Beryl and Sapphire" is a popular manhua created by artist Ocarina. Here includes protagonists with the most random names in history — the mild-mannered Beryl (Green) and the easily-embarrassed Sapphire (Blue). At times the closest of friends, at others the worst of enemies… In this donghua where each episode is set in a different world, how would they encounter each other time and again? ? Only angst? Too painful! Nothing but fluff? Too sugary! Come watch B&S, the show where you'll never guess the ending…
Kui Cheng Shoufu Cong Youxi Kaishi

Finding himself back in time 10 years ago, though technically an almost parallel world in 2009, Pei Qian got a system where he gets money to run his business. The funds for business and personal use are separated. After a set period, he can earn his personal funds according to how much his business funds he has left. The catch? Pei Qian earns more when he makes a loss in his business funds. Happily thinking how easy it would be, with many failed start-ups proving a point, Pei Qian founded his company Tengda and achieved financial freedom through the losses. Unfortunately, fate has other plans for him.
